{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["PBR Specular"], "type": "title", "extent": [0, 17], "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "extent": [95, 140], "text": ["Produce a normalized reflection bsdf."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [140, 325], "text": ["This node will produce a normalized (reflectivity of 1) reflection bsdf.\nShaders using this bsdf should adjust the reflectivity by multiplying the\ncomponent by an intensity parameter."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [370, 628], "text": ["The mathematical model used to simulate glossy reflections. For each viewing angle and surface normal, the model defines from which directions and at what intensity light is reflected. This is what shapes specular highlights and reflections in general."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [628, 878], "text": ["The overall glossiness, and with it the size of highlights, is controlled by ", {"text": ["Roughness"], "type": "ui"}, ". The available models simulate the effects caused by ", {"text": ["Roughness"], "type": "ui"}, " with varying degrees of physical accuracy, with GGX currently being the most accurate."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [878, 1053], "text": ["The chosen model has no effect when ", {"text": ["Roughness"], "type": "ui"}, " is ", {"text": ["0"], "type": "code"}, ", since this causes light to be reflected from a single direction at full intensity, making the model irrelevant."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1053, 1098], "text": ["See ", {"text": ["Roughness"], "type": "ui"}, " for more information."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1098, 1211], "text": [{"text": ["The figure below shows the result produced by various specular models across a range of roughness values."], "type": "em"}]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1211, 1363], "text": [{"text": ["Note how rough surfaces look more natural with the GGX model because the interaction of light with the rough surface is modeled more accurately."], "type": "em"}]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1363, 1409], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/nodes/vop/spec_model.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/nodes/vop/spec_model.png"}]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Specular Model"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "model"}, "extent": [337, 354], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1442, 1581], "text": ["Specifies a label for the BSDF component. This can be used to export\n    contributions from this component to a separate image plane."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Component Label"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "label"}, "extent": [1409, 1426], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1608, 1983], "text": ["This is a measure of how bumpy a surface is at the microscopic level. The most obvious effect is that reflections become glossier as ", {"text": ["Roughness"], "type": "ui"}, " increases. At a value of ", {"text": ["0"], "type": "code"}, ", the surface is perfectly smooth and produces perfect mirror reflections. A value of ", {"text": ["1"], "type": "code"}, " simulates a very rough surface, which results in very blurry reflections, similar to diffuse reflection."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1983, 2389], "text": ["In more accurate ", {"text": ["Specular Models"], "type": "ui"}, " like ", {"text": ["GGX"], "type": "code"}, ", reflections on rough surfaces are also darkened at grazing angles. This is due to Masking-Shadowing effects, where parts of the surface are hidden from view and/or not reached by light due to microscopic grooves and spikes in the surface. Note that this is simulated using a simplified mathematical model, rather than using actual additional geometry."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2389, 2467], "text": ["The visual change when transitioning from ", {"text": ["0"], "type": "code"}, " to ", {"text": ["1"], "type": "code"}, " is close to linear."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2467, 2531], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/nodes/vop/pbrspecular_rough_dielectric.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/nodes/vop/pbrspecular_rough_dielectric.png"}]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2531, 2593], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/nodes/vop/pbrspecular_rough_metallic.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/nodes/vop/pbrspecular_rough_metallic.png"}]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Roughness"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "rough"}, "extent": [1581, 1592], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [828, 922], "text": ["Causes reflections to be stretched in the direction defined by ", {"text": ["Anisotropy Direction"], "type": "ui"}, "."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [922, 1081], "text": ["This simulates microscopic bumps with a directional bias, causing light to be scattered more in the defined direction. This is typical of brushed metals."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1081, 1140], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/nodes/vop/principled_shader_aniso.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/nodes/vop/principled_shader_aniso.png"}]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2675, 2728], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/nodes/vop/pbrspecular_aniso.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/nodes/vop/pbrspecular_aniso.png"}]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "extent": [1169, 1286], "text": ["The effect of this parameter increases with ", {"text": ["Roughness"], "type": "ui"}, ". It has no effect at all when ", {"text": ["Roughness"], "type": "ui"}, " is ", {"text": ["0.0"], "type": "code"}, "."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Anisotropy"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "aniso"}, "extent": [2593, 2605], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "extent": [1312, 1640], "text": ["Controls the direction of ", {"text": ["Anisotropy"], "type": "ui"}, " relative to the UV coordinates of the surface. At ", {"text": ["0.0"], "type": "code"}, ", reflections are stretched in the ", {"text": ["U"], "type": "ui"}, " direction. At ", {"text": ["0.5"], "type": "code"}, ", the direction is rotated by ", {"text": ["90 degrees"], "type": "code"}, " to the ", {"text": ["V"], "type": "ui"}, " direction. ", {"text": ["1.0"], "type": "code"}, " equals ", {"text": ["180"], "type": "code"}, " degrees. Since the effect is symmetrical this produces the same result as ", {"text": ["0.0"], "type": "code"}, "."]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "extent": [1640, 1829], "text": ["The direction of rotation also depends on the UV layout. When the UVs are layed out such that textures appear on the surface without mirroring, higher values rotate counter-clockwise."]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "extent": [1829, 1891], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/nodes/vop/principled_shader_anisodir.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/nodes/vop/principled_shader_anisodir.png"}]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "extent": [1891, 1986], "text": ["The effect of this parameter diminishes with decreasing ", {"text": ["Roughness"], "type": "ui"}, " and ", {"text": ["Anisotropy"], "type": "ui"}, "."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Anisotropy Direction"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "anisodir"}, "extent": [2789, 2811], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2896, 3013], "text": ["Enables the geometric masking term of the ", {"text": ["GGX Specular Model"], "type": "ui"}, ", see ", {"text": ["Roughness"], "type": "ui"}, " for a detailed explanation."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Masking"], "role": "item", "extent": [2887, 2896], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [3026, 3271], "text": ["Controls the reflectance of surfaces facing the viewer. In other words, when a point on a surface has a normal pointing straight at the viewer, it has this reflectivity. This is often called ", {"text": ["F0"], "type": "ui"}, ", for reflectance at ", {"text": ["0\u00b0"], "type": "code"}, " from the viewer."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [3271, 3397], "text": ["Surfaces facing ", {"text": ["90\u00b0"], "type": "code"}, " degrees away from the viewer, as seen at the edges of rounded objects, are always 100% reflective."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [3397, 3595], "text": ["At high ", {"text": ["Roughness"], "type": "ui"}, " values, the effect discribed above is diffused, because it is applied at the microfacet level within the ", {"text": ["GGX"], "type": "ui"}, " model. See ", {"text": ["Roughness"], "type": "ui"}, " for a more detailed explanation."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Reflectance"], "role": "item", "extent": [3013, 3026], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Parameters", "role": "section", "extent": [325, 337], "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "id": "parameters"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [3608, 3698], "text": ["The normalized surface normal. When not connected, the global ", {"text": ["N"], "type": "ui"}, " is used instead."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["nN"], "extent": [3603, 3608], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [3702, 3795], "text": ["The normalized viewing direction. When not connected, the global ", {"text": ["I"], "type": "ui"}, " is used instead."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["nI"], "extent": [3698, 3702], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [3815, 3959], "text": ["The main surface tangent. This is used to compute the direction of anisotropy, ", {"text": ["anisodir"], "type": "ui"}, " is relative to the orientation of this vector."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [3959, 4021], "text": ["Must be normalized and tangential to the shaded surface."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [4030, 4149], "text": ["The ", {"text": ["Compute Tangents VOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/computetan", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/computetan"}, " offers various methods of computing suitable surface tangents."]}], "indent": 4, "role": "item", "extent": [4021, 4030], "container": true, "type": "tip"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "tip_group"}], "indent": 0, "text": ["utan"], "attrs": {"id": "utan"}, "extent": [3795, 3801], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [4169, 4266], "text": ["The surface bitangent. Must be normalized and perpendicular to both ", {"text": ["baseN"], "type": "ui"}, " and ", {"text": ["utan"], "type": "ui"}, "."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [4275, 4394], "text": ["The ", {"text": ["Compute Tangents VOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/computetan", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/computetan"}, " offers various methods of computing suitable surface tangents."]}], "indent": 4, "role": "item", "extent": [4266, 4275], "container": true, "type": "tip"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "tip_group"}], "indent": 0, "text": ["vtan"], "attrs": {"id": "vtan"}, "extent": [4149, 4155], "container": true, "type": "dt"}], "container": true, "type": "dt_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Inputs", "role": "section", "extent": [3595, 3603], "container": true, "type": "inputs_section", "id": "inputs"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [4407, 4433], "text": ["The reflection BSDF."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["f"], "extent": [4403, 4407], "container": true, "type": "dt"}], "container": true, "type": "dt_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Outputs", "role": "section", "extent": [4394, 4403], "container": true, "type": "outputs_section", "id": "outputs"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [4442, 4471], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/pbrdiffuse", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/pbrdiffuse"}]}], "container": true, "type": "bullet_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Related", "role": "section", "extent": [4433, 4442], "container": true, "type": "related_section", "id": "related"}], "title": ["PBR Specular"], "summary": ["Produce a normalized reflection bsdf."], "attrs": {"version": "3.0", "since": "14.5", "namespace": null, "internal": "pbrspecular", "context": "vop", "type": "node"}, "included": ["/nodes/vop/standard_shading_parms"], "type": "root"}